HEADWORD: Impurple
<hw>Im*pur"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Impurpled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Impurpling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> in + <ets>purple</ets>. Cf. <er>Empurple</er>.]</ety>
<def>To color or tinge with purple; to make red or reddish; to purple;
<as>as, a field <ex>impurpled</ex> with blood</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Impurpled</qex> with celestial roses, smiled.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The silken fleece <qex>impurpled</qex> for the loom.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imputability</ent>⟦br⟧
